Key Match Events: Ireland sealed a shock T20 World Cup win over England by five runs.
The match was interrupted and eventually abandoned due to rain, with England five runs short of their target according to the DLS scoring system.
Ireland's captain Andy Balbirnie scored 62 runs, contributing significantly to their total of 157 all out.
Liam Livingstone and Mark Wood each took three wickets for England.
Ireland's Balbirnie and Lorcan Tucker shared an 82-run stand.
England's batting lineup struggled, slumping to 29 for three with just one boundary in the first five overs.
Post-Match Reflections: Man-of-the-match Andy Balbirnie expressed that the victory was amazing and kind of emotional.
Balbirnie mentioned that the win would do a lot to grow the game back home in Ireland.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain interrupted play multiple times, ultimately leading to the match being abandoned.
England were among the tournament favourites and now face a tough test against holders Australia.
